##How many beds are there in Wuhan? We did the math

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Wu Yinfang, Chae Rim and Lu Yan, _ thepaper.cn _

In recent days, information about the requisition of some school dormitories in Wuhan has caused a heated discussion among netizens. Behind all this talk is the acquisition of school dormitories by Wuhan's new pneumonia prevention and control command. As more and more new cases of coronary pneumonia have been diagnosed in Wuhan, the beds in designated hospitals and the three shelter hospitals already in use are no longer sufficient, so another 12"shelter hospitals" have been built one after another, school dormitories have also been requisitioned.

According to the "notice on further regulating the admission and treatment of pneumonia patients in designated hospitals" issued by the medical treatment team of the Wuhan New Pneumonia Prevention and Control Command on February 5, and public media reports, at present, we have learned that there are several gradients in the current admission of patients: designated hospitals are mainly used for the admission and treatment of severe, critical and suspected critical cases; shelter hospitals are mainly used for the admission and treatment of patients with minor illnesses; and the dormitories of schools that have been requisitioned, some are treated as medical sites for mild cases and others as isolation sites for close contacts and suspected patients.

More than a dozen dorms have been commandeered to make room for 11,455 beds

On February 7, at the 17th press conference on the prevention and control of the new coronavirus epidemic in Hubei Province, Hu Yabo, standing committee member of the Wuhan Municipal Party Committee and Executive Vice Mayor, revealed that, the new campus of the Party School of the CPC Provincial Committee and four universities in Wuhan (Kong Hon University, Wuhan Business School, Wuhan Vocational College of Software and Engineering, Wuhan City Vocational College) will be transformed into designated medical sites for the treatment of patients with confirmed mild illness. In addition, the Chutian metropolis daily reported that six secondary vocational schools directly under the Wuhan Education Bureau, as well as several other vocational schools, as well as the old campus of the provincial Party School, were used as places of concentrated quarantine for Disease Prevention and control. About 11,455 beds have been built in more than 10 schools, including about 6,900 in designated medical sites and 4,555 in centralized isolation sites.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In order for the dormitory to be an isolation point and a medical point, it still needs some necessary materials and special transformation, and makes a plan according to the principle of "one school one policy" .

Some schools are equipped with supplies for each bed. Taking Wuhan City Vocational College as an example, each room has an independent toilet, air conditioning and other facilities, free of charge to provide six sets of bedding, 13 kinds of daily necessities 14 pieces: 1 Bucket, 1 Basin, 1 water bottle, 1 toothpaste, 1 toothbrush, wash Cup 1, Toilet Roll 1 tube, trash 1, garbage bag 1 roll, hand sanitizer 1 bottle, slippers (cloth)1 pair, slippers (sandals)1 pair, 2 towels.

According to a previous Beijing News report, Wuhan Business School dormitory to be renovated. In addition to the addition of a 380V high voltage for medical devices, the toilet and septic tank system will be modified to ensure that the excreta of the quarantined population is sterilized and excreted. More importantly, because the student's bed is "under the bed cabinet" structure, so the bed body 4 legs "saw off" , convenient for patients up and down. The school's handling of a series of thoughtful measures, but "Sawing Machine" action in the future will give students some problems, I hope the school can take into account, and reasonable disposal.

15"shelter hospitals" provide tens of thousands of beds

In addition to the Wembley Arena (800 beds) , the Wuhan Living Room (2,000 beds) and the Wuhan International Convention and Exhibition Center (1,600 beds) , which have been built and put into use since February 3, another 12 are under construction. There will be 11,600 beds available at 15"shelter hospitals" (this figure does not include the two "shelter hospitals" for which data are not available) . "Shelter Hospital" is mainly used to treat patients with confirmed mild illness.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
More than 10,000 beds in 35"designated hospitals" are at the forefront of the fight against the epidemic

According to the official website of Wuhan Health Commission since February 1, "the use of hospital beds in designated hospitals in the city, " the data show that the number of designated hospitals and their beds has been increasing.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
As of February 10, Wuhan had opened 35 designated hospitals with 12,437 beds, including 803 beds at Mount Thor and 88 beds at Mount Vulcan. According to previous reports, Thor Mountain and Vulcan Mountain hospital a total of 2,500 beds. So, together with the unoccupied "Ryōkami-san" beds, the 35 designated hospitals have a total capacity of 14,046 beds, mainly for critical, critical and suspected critical cases.

Based on the above public data, we know that Wuhan will have about 37,101 beds by the time all the renovations are completed, including the designated hospitals, the shelter hospitals and the school dormitories that have been requisitioned, about 32,546 beds are available for the treatment of confirmed cases. In addition to the old campus of the provincial Party School and more than a dozen vocational schools that have been published, there are isolated spots such as hotels and communities, but there is not much public data on them, so they are not included in the statistics.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Note: The above is based on some of the data that has been disclosed is not complete statistics, for community quarantine points and other quarantine points are not included in the statistics

Sources: Wuhan Municipal Health Commission official website, Hubei Provincial Government of the People's Republic of China official website, Chutian metropolis daily, sina.com, Hsinking daily website, Changjiang daily, Wuhan published, media reported publicly

Data as of 1400 GMT, 12 February 2020
